---
description: Security best practices and vulnerability prevention
globs: **/*.{ts,tsx,js,jsx}
alwaysApply: true
---

# Authentication
- NEVER store tokens in localStorage (XSS vulnerable)
- Use httpOnly, secure, SameSite cookies for sessions
- Implement proper token refresh logic
- Validate ALL inputs with Zod on both client AND server

# XSS Prevention
- Sanitize user-generated HTML (DOMPurify)
- Use dangerouslySetInnerHTML ONLY when necessary, always sanitize
- href values from users must be validated (javascript: protocol attack)

# CSRF Protection
- Use CSRF tokens for state-changing operations
- Validate Origin/Referer headers

# Dependency Security
- NO deprecated or unmaintained packages
- Run npm audit regularly, fix high/critical vulnerabilities
- Pin exact versions in package.json for security patches

# Secrets Management
- NO secrets in code, ever
- Use environment variables, validate at startup
- .env.example committed, .env in .gitignore
- Different secrets for dev/staging/prod

# API Security
- Rate limiting on all endpoints
- Input validation on every request
- SQL injection prevention (parameterized queries only)
- Error messages must not leak stack traces or DB structure in production
